item.body: I have played a lot of golf over the last 50 years. Started playing with Star flite and Canada Cup, Wilson Ultra and all those hard balls like Pinnacle. Then I got better and move the ladder of better balls till I reached the level of play Titleist was commanding. Needless to say, Titleist didn't  like bad swing and scars where coming fast when your hitting was not up to the task! I have tried lots of other company products like Taylor Made, Bridgestone, Callaway but would always come back to Titleist... until I got my hands on a Srixon. I started with a Z Star, but it was too soft. Tried the Z Star XV and it was good but a little on the firm side. Then they launched the Diamond and, bingo!, that was the one! It's flight suits my game as not only it flies higher but, surprinsingly, also longer with the driver. With shorter clubs, the spin is still there, even with the mid irons. Not the spinniest around the greens, but it does stop quickly enough to get in close range of the pins. I play Srixon ZX 5 mark II and the combination of the ball and the clubs is helping my game, no doubt about that.
item.title: Great ball at a cheaper price

teamRelationships.teamName: Nevada Bob's Golf - Canada Retail Employees

item.body: I used to play Vokey wedges but when I discovered RTX wedges, I replaced the former by the later in a hurry. Better distance control, more spin from full, half and quarter swing, good looking, especially in black satin! And as Ping did it with Hydropearl, Cleveland put Hydrazip on the RTX for better results when playing in wet conditions. I play 48 (mid bounce), 54 (high bounce) and 60 (mid bounce) and I can't see when I'll let go thoses wedges from my bag.

item.body:
I play a lot of golf.  I owned an Apple Ultra Watch for about a year but wanted the dedicated golf app and more advanced features.  I’m so glad I made the switch.

The Garmin Fenix 7 Pro Titanium is the best watch I have ever owned. The solar is awesome, the golf app is so accurate. This watch utilizes every GPS configuration available for maximum accuracy, while still maintaining great battery life!

I average about 15 GPS tracked hours per week and still get 10 days or so in between charges. I expect to pick up a tad bit more with the solar heading into the summer!

If you’re looking for a tough, rugged, do everything watch. This is it. It tracks anything you can think of. It’s also helped me manage my stress better on a daily basis. 

I would recommend this to anyone looking to improve themselves in anything. From Golf to general health. 

Titanium Bezel, Sapphire Crystal, and the best strap changing setup in the industry.

A winner from Garmin!

item.body: I had purchased this product because my cousins swear it was the greatest thing since sliced bread. Yes, it is a cool gadget and simulator, but it's not consistent. My first issue was when I was using it I didn't have enough lighting (fair enough). When I brought it the driving range with better lighting it worked, but it didn't pick up all my shots (not a problem). I'm using it more often with proper lighting and all at work on my down time and using both the recommended Rapsodo Callaway balls, range balls, and even foam practice balls and AGAIN all are not consistently getting picked up by this product. I'm not too sure if I had just gotten a bad unit, but I definitely wish I had gotten the Garmen R10 which on the plus side would have synced with my Garmen S70 watch. Overall, I really wouldn't recommend this product to anyone.
item.title: Overhype

comments.body: Hi Chris, I am sorry to hear about some of your issues.  I am sure we can figure out what is causing some of the inconsistencies.  Feel free to reach out to our support team at support@rapsodo.com.  We would love to look into it and figure out how we can get your experience to match the thousands of users who are loving their MLM2PRO!

Hi Chris, just wanted to follow up on this.  After reviewing with our support team, it looks like the alignment from the unit to the ball is a bit off in your sessions.  The MLM2PRO should sit 6.5-8ft behind the ball.  You will be able to use both the shot vision with the line and yellow alignment box, as well at the impact vision camera to make sure the ball is in the frame.  Our support team sent an email to you but never received a response.  We would love to test out the proper alignment with you and see if that will fix your readings.

item.body:
I ordered the set on Sunday night and they were delivered to my front porch by Wednesday.  That is excellent order fulfillment.  The unboxing was excellent - the clubs and bag looks awesome!  The packaging is outstanding, truly impressed! I cannot wait to get these clubs out on the course.  I'll definitely update this review as soon as I have a chance to hit them.  I have read issues with the club covers being "cheap", I disagree.  Head covers were provided for the Driver, 3w, 5w, 4H and putter.  All seem to work well and are of nice quality.  I ordered a set of Craftsman Iron Covers for the Irons that fit well, functionally and aesthetically with the clubs and bag.  If I have one criticism of the bag, it is the bag is no longer delivered with a "weather cover".  Per Stix, they cut costs by eliminating it and allowing customers to requisition a cover of their choice.  Stix mentioned they expect to provide one for purchase in the future.  This is a small issue compared to the overall package.  I'll let you know how they work on the course and how the black coating holds up to use.  

I did get fitted a week ago at a Callaway event.  Callaway also offers a military discount (Thank you).  However, the equivalent set would cost me over $2,300.   The "equivalent" set would not have a 3w or 5w etiher.  I am not a low digit golfer.  For "bang" for the buck, this set seems to far exceed other major manufactures (again, I still need to hit them on the course/range).  

Very happy so far with my purchase.  Well done Stix.    

UPDATE:  I have had the clubs to the range and played 18-holes at Myrtle Beach.  This was definitely the right purchase for me.  For the first time in years I hit my driver from the tee on all holes (except par 3's of course).  I am glad this set has a 3W and 5W.  I used them both on the greens.  The 4H is nice, but I am happy to have the 3W & 5W.  The Irons are great as well.  It also helps that I sunk a 20-ft putt on my first time putting the new putter...  shear luck, but gave me tons of confidence in my game.  Spent the next day at PopStroke in MB and used the putter there for four rounds.  Again, I have so many great things to say about this set of clubs.  I'll post up some pics after a few more rounds to show folks how the black coating wears on the club heads.

item.body: I finally got to play my first round with these and was very impressed. I didn't have any connectivity issues, they were easy to pair with my clubs, and the used my iPhone to pick up the shot tracking. I don't think it missed a single drive, iron, or wedge shot I was very pleased. Putting was a bit trickier because it would pick up phantom puts, so I had to manually adjust either from my phone or watch, which wasn't a big deal once I noticed it happening. The app is also very useful, I love that courses are downloaded prior to the round so it's quick to get a distance on your shot. We also were comparing the distance on the app vs a range finder and it was always within 5-7 yards, which for me is close enough. You only get to try a product first one time and I was blown away with the experience. If you are on the fence about these, just go for it, you won't be upset you did it.
item.title: incredible tracker

item.body: At this price point and feature list, it is hard to compete with the MLM2Pro. The next step up will cost you thousands for about the same data or less and slightly better simulation/integration. Albeit, it is not perfect (occasional connection issues, MLM2Pro app can be finicky) but it has so much to offer! It can provide you baseline numbers to get your clubs dialed in and also provide simulation capabilities via in-app or Awesome Golf or E6 Connect. The in-app practice mode can record both DTL and Face On views, the Combine mode can help you lower your hcp, RCT balls dial-in your spin rate/axis, and so much more. I'll be hardpressed to find an alternative to this at the price point and feature list. 9/10
item.title: Feature packed! Budget friendly!
